<subSubSection id="E6B66504FF92FF9DE9FBFE5FFD99FD82" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="AE13368FFF92FF9DE9FBFE5FFD99FD82" blockId="13.[151,1437,397,1138]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF92FF9DE9FBFE5FFEDBFE60" bold="true" box="[199,334,463,488]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Etymology.</emphasis>
A composed Latin noun (nigri + genu), meaning “black-knee”, in reference to the dark markings on the middle portion of the legs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E6B66504FF92FF9DE9FBFD82FD32FD57" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="AE13368FFF92FF9DE9FBFD82FD32FD57" blockId="13.[151,1437,397,1138]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF92FF9DE9FBFD82FED4FDA3" bold="true" box="[199,321,530,555]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The embolic disc and embolus of 
<taxonomicName id="69AC4D0CFF92FF9DEBDBFD83FCEDFDA3" authority="Ruiz, 2017" authorityName="Ruiz" authorityYear="2017" box="[743,888,531,555]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrigenu" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF92FF9DEBDBFD83FCEDFDA3" box="[743,888,531,555]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">A. nigrigenu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="87EB57E6FF92FF9DEAB8FD82FC76FDA3" box="[900,995,530,555]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" rank="species">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF92FF9DEAB8FD82FC76FDA3" bold="true" box="[900,995,530,555]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="69AC4D0CFF92FF9DEC38FD83FAE4FDA3" authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1967" box="[1284,1393,530,555]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="duckei">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF92FF9DEC38FD83FAE4FDA3" box="[1284,1393,530,555]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">A. duckei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="69AC4D0CFF92FF9DECB8FD83FF69FDC6" authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1967" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="santanae">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF92FF9DECB8FD83FF69FDC6" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">A. santanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="69AC4D0CFF92FF9DE831FDA7FE2BFDC7" authorityName="Galvis" authorityYear="2017" box="[269,446,566,591]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colombianus">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF92FF9DE831FDA7FE2BFDC7" box="[269,446,566,591]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">A. colombianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="69AC4D0CFF92FF9DE8C7FDA7FDE7FDC7" authority="Ruiz, 2017" authorityName="Ruiz" authorityYear="2017" box="[507,626,566,591]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF92FF9DE8C7FDA7FDE7FDC7" box="[507,626,566,591]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">A. simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="87EB57E6FF92FF9DEB40FDA6FD4CFDC7" box="[636,729,566,591]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" rank="species">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF92FF9DEB40FDA6FD4CFDC7" bold="true" box="[636,729,566,591]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
: there are two dPED and the vPED is proximal and projects retrolaterally; also, the embolus is thicker and sickle-shaped in these species (
<figureCitation id="36972A0AFF92FF9DEAC6FDCAFBD8FDFB" box="[1018,1101,602,627]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1915,1937]" captionTargetBox="[206,1426,223,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,193,1934]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 12. Amphidraus nigrigenu sp. nov. A left male palp, prolateral view; B same, dorsal view; C same, ventral view; D same, retrolateral view. CC, cymbial conductor; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; E, embolus; ED, embolic disc; RTA, retrolateral tibial apopHysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apopHysis; SD, sperm duct; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855471/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
C). However, 
<taxonomicName id="69AC4D0CFF92FF9DEDD4FDCBFAE1FDFB" authority="Ruiz, 2017" authorityName="Ruiz" authorityYear="2017" box="[1256,1396,603,627]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrigenu" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF92FF9DEDD4FDCBFAE1FDFB" box="[1256,1396,603,627]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">A. nigrigenu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="87EB57E6FF92FF9DEC46FDCAFF5DFD1F" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" rank="species">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF92FF9DEC46FDCAFF5DFD1F" bold="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished by the short and rounded RvTA with two teeth on the border (
<figureCitation id="36972A0AFF92FF9DEDBAFDEEFB4CFD1F" box="[1158,1241,638,663]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1915,1937]" captionTargetBox="[206,1426,223,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,193,1934]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 12. Amphidraus nigrigenu sp. nov. A left male palp, prolateral view; B same, dorsal view; C same, ventral view; D same, retrolateral view. CC, cymbial conductor; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; E, embolus; ED, embolic disc; RTA, retrolateral tibial apopHysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apopHysis; SD, sperm duct; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855471/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
D), being slender and sinuous in 
<taxonomicName id="69AC4D0CFF92FF9DE878FD33FE38FD33" authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1967" box="[324,429,674,699]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="duckei">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF92FF9DE878FD33FE38FD33" box="[324,429,674,699]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">A. duckei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="69AC4D0CFF92FF9DE8DBFD33FD03FD33" authorityName="Galvis" authorityYear="2017" box="[487,662,674,699]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colombianus">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF92FF9DE8DBFD33FD03FD33" box="[487,662,674,699]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">A. colombianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, short with one tooth in 
<taxonomicName id="69AC4D0CFF92FF9DEA8DFD33FBA2FD33" authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1967" box="[945,1079,675,699]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="santanae">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF92FF9DEA8DFD33FBA2FD33" box="[945,1079,675,699]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">A. santanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="CA3D4B7EFF92FF9DED49FD32FA87FD33" author="Galiano" box="[1141,1298,674,699]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" refString="Galiano, M. E. (1967) Dos nuevas especies del genero Amphidraus Simon, 1900 (Araneae, Salticidae). Physis Buenos Aires (C), 27, 95 - 100." type="journal article" year="1967">Galiano 1967</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 4), and finger-shaped in 
<taxonomicName id="69AC4D0CFF92FF9DE868FD57FE5CFD57" authority="Ruiz, 2017" authorityName="Ruiz" authorityYear="2017" box="[340,457,710,735]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF92FF9DE868FD57FE5CFD57" box="[340,457,710,735]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">A. simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="87EB57E6FF92FF9DE8F3FD56FDBCFD57" box="[463,553,710,735]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" rank="species">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF92FF9DE8F3FD56FDBCFD57" bold="true" box="[463,553,710,735]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation id="36972A0AFF92FF9DEB04FD56FD16FD57" box="[568,643,710,735]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1889,1911]" captionTargetBox="[218,1360,194,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,193,1867]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 14. Amphidraus simplex sp. nov. A left male palp, prolateral view; B same, dorsal view; C same, ventral view; D same, retrolateral view; E epigyne, ventral view; F same, cleared, ventral view. CC, cymbial conductor; CO, copulatory opening; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; E, embolus; ED, embolic disc; FD, fertilization duct; po, coupling pocket; PS, primary spermatHeca; RvTA, retroventral tibial apopHysis; SD, sperm duct; SS, secondary spermatHeca; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855479/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Fig 14</figureCitation>
D).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E6B66504FF92FF9DE9FBFD7AFE37FC65" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" type="description">
<paragraph id="AE13368FFF92FF9DE9FBFD7AFE59FC43" blockId="13.[151,1437,397,1138]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF92FF9DE9FBFD7AFD5CFC8B" bold="true" box="[199,713,746,771]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">
Description. Male 
<typeStatus id="7117882DFF92FF9DE89EFD7AFD9CFC8B" box="[418,521,746,771]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">holotype</typeStatus>
(
