</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AE13368FFF92FF9DE9FBFB86FB33FBFA" blockId="13.[151,1437,397,1138]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF92FF9DE9FBFB86FE93FBA7" bold="true" box="[199,262,1046,1071]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Note.</emphasis>
Although we have found large variation in male palp structure of 
<taxonomicName id="69AC4D0CFF92FF9DEAC4FB87FBE8FBA6" authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1967" box="[1016,1149,1047,1070]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="santanae">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF92FF9DEAC4FB87FBE8FBA6" box="[1016,1149,1047,1070]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">A. santanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which could include the palp of the 
<typeStatus id="7117882DFF92FF9DE826FBA7FEE9FBD8" box="[282,380,1079,1104]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="69AC4D0CFF92FF9DE898FBA8FDA4FBD8" authorityName="Ruiz" authorityYear="2017" box="[420,561,1080,1104]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrigenu">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF92FF9DE898FBA8FDA4FBD8" box="[420,561,1080,1104]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">A. nigrigenu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we preferred to recognize this male as a different species, since the unusual morphology of the palp is accompanied by a different color pattern in legs and palps (black).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
